task

lines <- 
c(
  "Whose woods these are I think I know.",
  "His house is in the village though;", 
  "He will not see me stopping here",
  "To watch his woods fill up with snow."
)

lines <- tibble(phrase = lines,
       id = 1:4)

lines_df <- lines %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, phrase)

lines_df %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>% 
  filter(n > 1) #all words repeated

task: most common pos neg and neutral words in emma

loughran <- get_sentiments("loughran")

book_emma <- tibble(
  text = emma,
  sentence = 1:length(emma)
) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>% 
  anti_join(stop_words)
Joining, by = "word"
emma_sentiments <- book_emma %>% 
  inner_join(loughran)
Joining, by = "word"
emma_sentiments %>% 
  filter(sentiment == "positive") %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE)

emma_sentiments %>% 
  filter(sentiment == "negative") %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE)

unique(loughran$sentiment)
[1] "negative"     "positive"     "uncertainty"  "litigious"    "constraining"
[6] "superfluous" 
emma_sentiments %>% 
  filter(sentiment != "positive" & 
           sentiment != "negative" ) %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE)
